  <Docs since="1">
    <summary>Wraps an existing <c><see cref="T:Java.IO.Reader" /></c> and counts the line terminators encountered
 while reading the data.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">Wraps an existing <c><see cref="T:Java.IO.Reader" /></c> and counts the line terminators encountered
 while reading the data. The line number starts at 0 and is incremented any
 time <c>'\r'</c>, <c>'\n'</c> or <c>"\r\n"</c> is read. The class has an
 internal buffer for its data. The size of the buffer defaults to 8 KB.
</para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/java/io/LineNumberReader.html" target="_blank">[Android Documentation]</a>
        </format>
      </para>
    </remarks>
    <since version="Added in API level 1" />
  </Docs>
